Here is the complete chronological history of your Sentinel Stack build. I have organized this into three distinct phases: Foundation, Intelligence, and Hardening.

Phase 1: Foundation (Environment & Monitoring)
We began by creating the directory structure and the core monitoring engine.

Create the Stack Directory:

Bash
mkdir ~/sentinel-stack && cd ~/sentinel-stack
Create the Sentry Engine (sentry.py):
This script monitors network interfaces (specifically utun for unauthorized VPNs/Tunnels).

Python
# ~/sentinel-stack/sentry.py
import os, subprocess, time  
def check_network():
    interfaces = subprocess.check_output(['ifconfig']).decode('utf-8')
    if 'utun' in interfaces:
        with open('forensic_history.log', 'a') as f:
            f.write(f"{time.ctime()}: Alert - utun interface detected!\n")
while True:
    check_network()
    time.sleep(10)
Establish the Baseline (today_training.log):
We captured your "Clean State" on March 27 to teach the AI what is normal.

Bash
ifconfig > ~/sentinel-stack/today_training.log
sw_vers >> ~/sentinel-stack/today_training.log
Phase 2: Intelligence (The AI Brain)
We integrated Ollama to turn raw logs into human-readable security analysis.

Define the Brain (SentinelModelfile):

Bash
cat <<EOF > ~/sentinel-stack/SentinelModelfile
FROM llama3.2:1b
SYSTEM """
You are the Sentinel-V2 DEFENSIVE BRAIN. 
Compare logs to the March 27 baseline.
RULE: If you see a threat, start with: COUNTERMEASURE_REQUIRED
"""
EOF
Train/Initialize the Brain:

Bash
ollama create sentinel-v2 -f ~/sentinel-stack/SentinelModelfile
Create the "Kill-Switch" (kill_switch.sh):

Bash
cat << 'EOF' > ~/sentinel-stack/kill_switch.sh
#!/zsh
networksetup -setnetworkserviceenabled Wi-Fi off
echo "$(date) - NETWORK KILLED BY SENTINEL" >> ~/sentinel-stack/forensic_history.log
EOF
chmod +x ~/sentinel-stack/kill_switch.sh
Phase 3: Hardening (The Fortress)
This is where we locked the system down using macOS-native security features.

Audit System Integrity (SIP):

Bash
csrutil status  # Confirmed: enabled
Verify Full Disk Access (TCC):

Bash
sudo sqlite3 "/Library/Application Support/com.apple.TCC/TCC.db" 'SELECT client FROM access WHERE service="kTCCServiceSystemPolicyAllFiles" AND auth_value=2'
Digital Signature (Code Signing):
We signed the script so the kernel knows it hasn't been tampered with.

Bash
sudo chflags nouchg ~/sentinel-stack/sentry.py
codesign --force -s - ~/sentinel-stack/sentry.py
The Immutable Lock (uchg):
This prevents even the 'root' user from deleting or modifying these files.

Bash
sudo chflags uchg ~/sentinel-stack/sentry.py
sudo chflags uchg ~/sentinel-stack/SentinelModelfile
The Terminal Dashboards (.zshrc Aliases):

Bash
